From: Eric Dumazet <edumazet@google.com>
Date: Fri, 7 Feb 2025 13:58:35 +0000
Subject: neighbour: use RCU protection in __neigh_notify()
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc3
Git-commit: becbd5850c03ed33b232083dd66c6e38c0c0e569
References: jsc#PED-10684 jsc#PED-11230 CVE-2025-21763 bsc#1237897

__neigh_notify() can be called without RTNL or RCU protection.

Use RCU protection to avoid potential UAF.

Fixes: 426b5303eb43 ("[NETNS]: Modify the neighbour table code so it handles multiple network namespaces")
Signed-off-by: Eric Dumazet <edumazet@google.com>
Reviewed-by: David Ahern <dsahern@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Kuniyuki Iwashima <kuniyu@amazon.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250207135841.1948589-4-edumazet@google.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 net/core/neighbour.c |    8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/core/neighbour.c
+++ b/net/core/neighbour.c
@@ -3447,10 +3447,12 @@ static const struct seq_operations neigh
 static void __neigh_notify(struct neighbour *n, int type, int flags,
 			   u32 pid)
 {
-	struct net *net = dev_net(n->dev);
 	struct sk_buff *skb;
 	int err = -ENOBUFS;
+	struct net *net;
 
+	rcu_read_lock();
+	net = dev_net_rcu(n->dev);
 	skb = nlmsg_new(neigh_nlmsg_size(), GFP_ATOMIC);
 	if (skb == NULL)
 		goto errout;
@@ -3463,9 +3465,11 @@ static void __neigh_notify(struct neighb
 		goto errout;
 	}
 	rtnl_notify(skb, net, 0, RTNLGRP_NEIGH, NULL, GFP_ATOMIC);
-	return;
+	goto out;
 errout:
 	rtnl_set_sk_err(net, RTNLGRP_NEIGH, err);
+out:
+	rcu_read_unlock();
 }
 
 void neigh_app_ns(struct neighbour *n)
